The paper focuses on the visual exploration of simulation models by multiple types of experts, which suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of simulation models also suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social impact (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of scatterplot matrices and linked views, which are common visualization techniques in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the exploration of trade-offs, which could be related to game theory (cs.GT) or cybersecurity (cs.CY).
